    {
      "id": "bAbO_j2NvrEcDsPmDXp1R",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -4.610881611628201,
      "y": 688.9994450537899,
      "width": 529.8451220510027,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "H3jSL4pyYct51bAw1WEeW",
      "index": "ae",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1121245822,
      "version": 1283,
      "versionNonce": 1646139085,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771551301329,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The data reveals a dynamic pattern in deployments over the past\nfew months, with notable fluctuations. In February 2026,\ndeployments started at **1,908** on the 1st and showed a\nsignificant increase, peaking at **3,314** on the 14th. This peak\nwas followed by a decline to **2,013** on the 15th, before rising\nagain to **2,694** by the 16th. This indicates a volatile trend\nwith sharp increases and decreases within short periods.\n\nComparing this to the same period in 2025, there was a similar\npattern of fluctuations, but the peaks and troughs were less\npronounced. For instance, on February 14, 2025, deployments were\n**1,779**, significantly lower than the same day in 2026. This\nsuggests an overall increase in deployment activity year-over-year,\nwith 2026 showing more intense spikes.\n\nThe data highlights a pattern of rapid changes in deployment\nnumbers, suggesting a highly responsive or volatile environment. The\nsharp increases and decreases could be indicative of external\nfactors influencing deployment needs or capabilities, reflecting a\ndynamic operational landscape.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The data reveals a dynamic pattern in deployments over the past few months, with notable fluctuations. In February 2026, deployments started at **1,908** on the 1st and showed a significant increase, peaking at **3,314** on the 14th. This peak was followed by a decline to **2,013** on the 15th, before rising again to **2,694** by the 16th. This indicates a volatile trend with sharp increases and decreases within short periods.\n\nComparing this to the same period in 2025, there was a similar pattern of fluctuations, but the peaks and troughs were less pronounced. For instance, on February 14, 2025, deployments were **1,779**, significantly lower than the same day in 2026. This suggests an overall increase in deployment activity year-over-year, with 2026 showing more intense spikes.\n\nThe data highlights a pattern of rapid changes in deployment numbers, suggesting a highly responsive or volatile environment. The sharp increases and decreases could be indicative of external factors influencing deployment needs or capabilities, reflecting a dynamic operational landscape.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
